# Mobile-First UI — Terminal & Platform (STRICT)

All Quasar UI for this product — **kiosk/terminal** and **platform** (workspace + admin) — is designed as a **phone app first**, then scaled up. Desktop is enhancement only.

## Non-negotiable

- Design **mobile-first**: default styles target `xs` / `sm`. Add `md` / `lg` refinements after the phone layout works.
- Every screen must be **fully responsive** with **no horizontal page scroll** on phone widths.
- Touch targets ≥ **44px** (prefer **48px** for primary actions). Dense desktop controls are allowed only as progressive enhancement, never as the only usable affordance.
- Prefer **single-column** flows on phone: stacked actions, full-width buttons, bottom sheets / maximized dialogs.
- Do **not** ship desktop-only tables, multi-column dashboards, or hover-only interactions as the primary UX.
- On `xs` / `sm`: replace wide `q-table` grids with **cards / lists** when columns will not fit; keep tables behind `gt-sm` when both exist.
- Dialogs and forms must fit a phone viewport (scrollable body, sticky footer actions when needed).
- Mental model: staff or owner using a **phone in one hand** (counter terminal or office).

## Surfaces

| Surface | Paths (typical) | Extra expectation |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Terminal / kiosk | `pages/kiosk/**`, `layouts/KioskLayout.vue`, terminal-facing session/customer dialogs | Counter phone/tablet; large primary actions |
| Platform workspace | `pages/workspace/**`, `layouts/WorkspaceLayout.vue` | Same mobile-first bar; drawer/nav must work on phone |
| Platform admin | `pages/admin/**`, `layouts/AdminLayout.vue` | Same rules; no admin exception for desktop-only layouts |

## Quasar patterns (required)

- Grid: `col-12` base, then `col-sm-*` / `col-md-*` / `col-lg-*`.
- Visibility: `lt-sm` / `lt-md` for mobile chrome; `gt-sm` / `gt-md` for desktop-only density.
- Spacing via Quasar helpers (`q-pa-*`, `q-col-gutter-*`); never pad `QLayout` / `QPageContainer` / `QDrawer` wrappers.
- Follow [`.agents/skills/quasar-ui-ux-design/SKILL.md`](../../.agents/skills/quasar-ui-ux-design/SKILL.md) for density, tokens, and touch hitboxes.

## Banned

- Fixed pixel widths that break below ~360px content width.
- Side-by-side critical actions that clip or wrap unreadably on phone.
- Hover-only menus/tooltips as the sole way to reach a required action.
- “Looks fine on desktop” as acceptance criteria without a phone-width check.
